-- Colombia Stocks: BVC, Petrominerales, Pacific Rubiales Energy
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-07-11T20:50:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/colombia-stocks-bvc-petrominerales-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.8 percent to 13,675.13 while the
Colcap Index increased 0.7 percent to 1,666.08.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia SA  (BVC CB), the operator of
the country’s main stock exchange, increased 2.8 percent to
29.30 pesos. The company said on its website  yesterday  that net
income rose 21 percent to 17.3 billion pesos ($9.7 million) in
the first six months of the year.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s largest oil company,
advanced 0.8 percent to 5,010 pesos. Construction on the
Bicentennial Pipeline will be completed Dec. 30, the Mines and
Energy Ministry said yesterday by e-mail. Ecopetrol, which
controls the pipeline, has said the project would be finished in
the fourth quarter.  Other oil producers gained in line with crude as the U.S.
Energy Department reported that supplies dropped.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates in the Andean region, rose 1.3 percent to 18,380
pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates
the country’s largest oil field, increased 1.4 percent to 39,880
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
